 <h3 class="mt-4 h-notes">
 Technical notes:
 </h3>
 <p>
 Currently, uploading MIDI files is allowed only for monophonic musical material. Polyphonic material, or MIDI files in which Note-On events occur before Note-Off events of the previous note, lead to incorrect model behavior.
 It is recommended to use MIDI format1; MIDI0 is not always fully supported regarding key signatures.
 Multitrack MIDI files are handled correctly if each track is monophonic. In that case, tracks will be processed sequentially, but their use is not recommended.
 Work on handling these limitations is planned. For now, to make a MIDI file comply with the stated requirement, use external software (MIDI or notation editors).
 </p>


